=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_MainMenu_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 400 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 400.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -15.9788
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5007
  pitch_clarity: 48.4231
  inharmonicity: 0.0003
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -6.2286
  resonance_freq: 409.1309

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: MainMenu Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/MainMenu.html
// Tags: MainMenu, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
~testTone = MenuAction("Test Tone", {
    { SinOsc.ar(400) * 0.1 }.play;
});

MainMenu.register(~testTone, "Tests");
)

MainMenu.unregister(~testTone); // to remove
